{
  "style": "IEEE",
  "texts": [
    "In this paper, we proposed a multimodal audio-image to video action recognition framework called the Multimodal Audio-image and Video Action Recognizer (MAiVAR).We generated several audio-image representations and compared their efficiency.",
    "We then extracted audio and visual features using CNN-based models and fused them.",
    "The framework achieves 87.91% accuracy on the UCF51 dataset and 79.01% accuracy on the Kinetics Sounds dataset.",
    "Experiments demonstrated that visual modalities are not indispensable.",
    "MAiVAR performed better in comparison with other baseline methods.Future research could focus on exploring different transformer-based architectures such as Video Transformer Network Architecture (VidTr) Neimark et al [44], with other optimal feature representations."
  ],
  "correct_citations": [
    "MAiVAR performed better in comparison with other baseline methods.Future research could focus on exploring different transformer-based architectures such as Video Transformer Network Architecture (VidTr) Neimark et al [44], with other optimal feature representations."
